{"type":"message","id":"60cb71ce","parentId":"5b88b4a0","timestamp":"2026-04-02T04:24:37.047Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the sessions_list results:\n1. The first session is the cron job itself (cron:3709e1d2...)\n2. The second session is a subagent that appears to have already completed its task (last message was assistant with a \"task completed\" message)\n\nThe subagent session was updated at 1775103650192, which is about 2-3 minutes ago from current time (1775103860796 - 1775103650192 = 210604ms ≈ 3.5 minutes).\n\nThis seems to be a subagent that completed the same learning task recently. Looking at its message content, it seems this subagent already ran and completed the self-learning task. The last message from the assistant in that session was about completing the task.\n\nThe question is: is there an \"active conversation\" with a USER message in the last 5 minutes? \n\nLooking at the sessions:\n- Session 1: cron job session - last message was an assistant tool call (the cron job itself)\n- Session 2: subagent session - last message was an assistant stop (looks like it completed)\n\nNeither shows a recent USER message in the last 5 minutes. The subagent's last activity was about 3.5 minutes ago, and that was the assistant's completion message, not a user message.\n\nHowever, the subagent session does have `lastChannel: \"feishu\"` which means it was communicating via Feishu. The question is whether there's an actual user conversation happening.\n\nGiven the context, it appears:\n- The cron job detected no active USER conversation in the last 5 minutes\n- A subagent had previously completed a similar self-learning task\n\nI should proceed with the self-learning task since there's no active user conversation. Let me search for the latest industry trends.","thinkingSignature":"464953f8c868d3b0d22a43b1f09f418e83ce16b339349a1eba0e7b3d041c77a0"},{"type":"text","text":"检测到当前无用户活跃对话（最近5分钟内无用户消息），执行自主学习。\n"},{"